responses: {"Q0":"Primarily chunking. It was easy to do when things were stepwise or arpeggiating; just pay attention to where the contour shifts direction. It was really hard when the melody didn't confirm the key, however; I could usually come up with a new key to justify the pattern or way of thinking about it (sometimes as a set of very local relationships), but it took longer and the more I had to think about it to come up with a framework for chunking, the more it interfered with my ability to simultaneously retain the melody."}
